# Intuition
Main goal is to determine the count of unique paths from the top-left corner to the bottom-right corner of a grid while accounting for obstacles in the grid. It uses dynamic programming to iteratively calculate the paths, avoiding obstacles and utilizing previously computed values to efficiently arrive at the final count.

This python solution beats 96%.
