# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
This is a DP question. Use DP in a standard way!
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
There is a similar question which can be solved by using Pascal traingle.
[Leetcode 62. Unique Paths](https://leetcode.com/problems/unique-paths/solutions/3602735/python-c-solutions-use-math-pascal-triangle-dp-beats-100/)

But in this question there are so many obstacleGrids, the direct applying of Math trick like Pascal Triangle is is not easy and does not bring benefits( language like python which has packages for computing combinations). It is suggested to use standardard DP to solve.

In fact, it is not difficult to know that
```
if (obstacleGrid[i][j]==1) return dp[i][j]=0;
```
In second approach, optimized 1D iterative DP is implemented which beats 100%.

The space complexity is reduced. Consider the transforms
```
dp[j]<-dp[i][j]
prev[j]<-dp[i-1][j]
```
Before the next iteration, don't forget ```prev=dp```! Such tricks are used  in such Pascal-triangle-like problems(Leetcode 118. Pascal's Triangle)
