Let's say we have the following field with obstacles:
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/olsh/image_1542205389.png)

Let's go through every cell and calculate how many paths are there to this cell.
First cell: we just stept into it. That's all => only one path.
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/olsh/image_1542205778.png)
Go to neighbor cells. One of them is obstacle. We mark it as 0 because in future, for calculating numbers or routes to other cells, they won't add anything.
Another cell is 1 because we can get there only from the first cell. 
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/olsh/image_1542207602.png)
Every other cell (i,j) will be sum of cells above (i-1,j) and left (i,j-1). For border cells (with indices (ai,0) and (0, bi)) we assume that one of neighbor cells is 0, so just copy number from other cell:
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/olsh/image_1542208046.png)

After it, we just get the number in the target cell.

Here is the code:
