solutions.content:
Hello Leetcoders, Hope you are doing well.

Let's solve this problem together.

**Problem statement :** 
We have a matrix and a robot. Initially robot is located at top-left corner (0,0) of the matrix and robot want's to go to destination bottom-right corner(m-1,n-1) index. Robot can only go right and bottom directions.

Find total no. of ways robot can go from source to destination index.

Follow-up : Their are some obstacles in the matrix which robot want's to avoid during his journey.

**Approach - backtracking :** 

Data we have
* Source and destination defined.
* Next step is defined -> right or bottom

```
class Solution {
    int count = 0;
    public int uniquePathsWithObstacles(int[][] grid) {
        int m = grid.length;
        int n = grid[0].length;

        // track all visited pos till now
        boolean[][] visited = new boolean[m][n];

        // if there are an obstacle at source or destination position
        if(grid[0][0] == 1 || grid[m-1][n-1] == 1) return 0;


        rb(grid, visited, m, n, 0, 0);

        return count;
    }

    private void rb(int[][] grid, boolean[][] visited, int m, int n, int i, int j) {
        // border conditions
        if(i < 0 || i >= m || j < 0 || j >= n || grid[i][j] == 1 || visited[i][j]) return;

        // is destination position
        if(i == m-1 && j == n-1) {
            count++;
            return;
        }

        // mark current pos visited
        visited[i][j] = true;

        rb(grid, visited, m, n, i, j+1); // go right
        rb(grid, visited, m, n, i+1, j); // go bottom;

        // backtracking
        visited[i][j] = false;
    }
}
```

This approach will show you TLE
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/2c10b5f3-d4fa-4c0a-bb6f-6c7983a61a42_1653043386.22838.png)

*Having TLE Means we have so many overlapping subproblem (which is obvious)*

**Approach : Recursive + Memoization + Bottom-Up**

Store the value for each position toi avoid overlapping-subproblem

```

class Solution {
    int count = 0;
    public int uniquePathsWithObstacles(int[][] grid) {
        int m = grid.length;
        int n = grid[0].length;

        // track all visited pos till now
        boolean[][] visited = new boolean[m][n];

        int dp[][] = new int[m][n]; // store values

        // if there are an obstacle at source or destination position
        if(grid[0][0] == 1 || grid[m-1][n-1] == 1) return 0;

        dp[m-1][n-1] = 1; // memorize the calculated values

        rb(grid, visited, m, n, 0, 0, dp); // recursive call

        return dp[0][0];
    }

    private int rb(int[][] grid, boolean[][] visited, int m, int n, int i, int j, int[][] dp) {
        // border conditions
        if(i < 0 || i >= m || j < 0 || j >= n || grid[i][j] == 1 || visited[i][j]) return 0;


        // is destination position
        if(i == m-1 && j == n-1) {
            // count++;
            return dp[i][j];
        }

        // if current position is already processed
        if(dp[i][j] != 0) return dp[i][j];

        // mark current pos visited
        visited[i][j] = true;

        int right = rb(grid, visited, m, n, i, j+1, dp); // go right
        int bottom = rb(grid, visited, m, n, i+1, j, dp); // go bottom;

        // backtracking
        visited[i][j] = false;

        dp[i][j] = right + bottom;
        return dp[i][j];
    }
}

