solutions.content:
```
Select id, date, people
From (
Select id, date, people,
    @rank:= If(people>=100, @rank+1, 0) AS Rank,
    @group:= If(@rank=0 or @rank=1, @group+1, @group) AS GroupNum
From stadium, (Select @rank:=0, @group:=0) var
) tmp

JOIN
(
    Select GroupNum
    From
        (
        Select id, date, people,
            @rank_:= If(people>=100, @rank_+1, 0) AS Rank,
            @group_:= If(@rank_=0 or @rank_=1, @group_+1, @group_) AS GroupNum
        From stadium, (Select @rank_:=0, @group_:=0) var
        ) tmp2
    Group By GroupNum
    Having count(*) >=3
) filter
ON tmp.GroupNum = filter.GroupNum;
```

Since MySQL 5.7 doesn't support CTE `WITH` clause, I can only repeat the subquery. Also note because the subquery with variable was used twice in the query, the variable name in the second subquery need change, otherwise looks like two subquery will interfere each other and the result is empty.

